    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>LEAD: To the Sports Editor:</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>LEAD: To the Sports Editor:</p>
        <p>To the Sports Editor:</p>
        <p>I am a 13-year old girl who enjoys watching and playing tennis. I recently read that Boris Becker stated he would take steroids and other performance-enhancing drugs if other players did, even if there were a possible risk. The Associated Press also quoted Becker as saying: ''But when you have to make a living, earn your money, you say, O.K., for the next two years I'm going to take drugs and make money. Then I would risk it.''</p>
        <p>It bothers me to see an athlete not concerned about his health or his sport and only concerned about money. Is this a good example to set for my generation? I hope that Boris Becker was misunderstood because if he meant what he said, he doesn't deserve to be an international sports hero.</p>
        <p>PAMELA STEPHANIE ROMAS</p>
        <p>Scarsdale, N.Y.</p>
      </block>
